'''Mariyam Afeefa''' is a Maldivian actress.
==Career== In 2010, Afeefa was featured in Abdul Fahtah's horror film ''[[Jinni (film)|Jinni]]'' alongside [[Ali Seezan]].<ref name=Jinni>{{cite news|url=http://www.haveeru.com.mv:80/?page=details&id=93070&category=ihUfinum |title=Positive comment for the film - Its a big achievement |language=Dhivehi |work=Haveeru |last=Naseer |first=Ismail |date=11 February 2010 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100212110900/http://www.haveeru.com.mv:80/?page=details&id=93070&category=ihUfinum |deadurl=yes |archivedate=19 September 2018 |accessdate=19 September 2018 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> Based on true incidents that occurred in an island of Maldives, she played the role of Thahumeena, a simple-going girl who romantically link ups with a visitor and a ghost who seduce the same person in the shape of Thahumeena. Prior to release the film was marketed to be "full of suspense" and "unique" compared to other mediocre Maldivian horror films. Upon release, the film received mixed reviews from critics; majority of them complaining for having the "same old feeling" of prior horror flicks though the performance were noted to be satisfactory. Despite the mixed reviews, the film witnessed a positive response at the box office, screening a total of twenty two housefull shows in Male', declaring it as a Mega-Hit.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.haveeru.com.mv:80/?page=details&id=95729&category=ihUfinum |title=Positive comment for the film - Its a big achievement |language=Dhivehi |work=Haveeru |last=Nadheem |first=Ahmed |date=29 April 2010 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100503053202/http://www.haveeru.com.mv:80/?page=details&id=95729&category=ihUfinum |deadurl=yes |archivedate=19 September 2018 |accessdate=19 September 2018 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> At the Enchanteur Maldives Film Awards 2012, Afeefa received a nomination for the Best Actress category.<ref name=MFA12nom>{{cite news|url=http://maldivesfilmawards.com/?page=detail&id=34 |title=Feature Film Nominations Announced |language=Dhivehi |work=Maldives Film Awards |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160417013119/http://maldivesfilmawards.com/?page=detail&id=34 |deadurl=yes |archivedate=30 March 2018 |accessdate=30 March 2018}}</ref>
Her first release of 2011, was Mohamed Aboobakuru's critical and commercial failure ''Hiyy Vindhaa Nulaa'', where her role in the film was regarded and "unnecessary" and "meaningless". It was followed by her playing the role of Sherin, the gluttonous wife who is after her husband's wealth, in the Moomin Fuad-directed crime tragedy drama ''[[Loodhifa]]''.<ref name=Loodhifa>{{cite news|url=https://sun.mv/5254 |title=Loodhifa; Up-righting the fraternal film industry |language=Dhivehi |work=Sun |last=Naif |first=Ahmed |date=15 February 2011 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140902184704/https://sun.mv/5254 |deadurl=no |archivedate=2 September 2014 |accessdate=16 April 2018}}</ref> Featuring an [[ensemble cast]], the film deals with current social issues in the society told from different perspectives of the characters.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://haveeru.com.mv/?page=details&id=104588&category=ihUfinum |title=Expectations for "Loodhifa" is high |language=Dhivehi |work=Haveeru |last=Nadheem |first=Ahmed |date=16 December 2010 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20101216122531/http://haveeru.com.mv/?page=details&id=104588&category=ihUfinum |deadurl=yes |archivedate=16 December 2010 |accessdate=3 October 2018}}</ref> Made on a budget of [[Maldivian rufiyaa|MVR]] 600,000, the film was declared a commercial failure though it received wide critical acclaim, praising the performance of cast and the film's "realism" in its language, characters and their attitude.<ref name=Loodhifa/> At the [[7th Gaumee Film Awards]] she was bestowed with her second [[Gaumee Film Award for Best Actress]].<ref name=GFA7won>{{cite news|url=https://mihaaru.com/entertainment/10616 |title=With 10 awards, "Loodhifa" crowned as Best Film |language=Dhivehi |work=Mihaaru |last=Adhushan |first=Ahmed |date=22 December 2016 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180331061412/https://mihaaru.com/entertainment/10616 |deadurl=no |archivedate=30 March 2018 |accessdate=30 March 2018}}</ref>
